---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Blog Tech - Notes"
    ,
    description="Las Notas son una forma de almacenar información importante y accesible en cualquier momento."
>
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 pt-10 pb-16">
        <div class="w-full">
            <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 flex items-center gap-2">
                Notes
                <span class="material-symbols-outlined text-green-500"
                    >description</span
                >
            </h1>
            <div class="space-y-8">
                <article
                    class="p-6 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800"
                >
                    <header class="mb-3">
                        <h2
                            class="text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark"
                        >
                            The power of component-based architecture
                        </h2>
                        <time
                            class="text-sm font-mono text-muted-light dark:text-muted-dark"
                            datetime="2024-07-21">July 21, 2024</time
                        >
                    </header>
                    <p
                        class="text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark/90"
                    >
                        Thinking about how breaking down UIs into reusable
                        components not only speeds up development but also
                        enforces consistency and makes maintenance a breeze.
                        It’s a simple concept with a profound impact on
                        scalability.
                    </p>
                </article>
                <article
                    class="p-6 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800"
                >
                    <header class="mb-3">
                        <h2
                            class="text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark"
                        >
                            A quick tip for centering in CSS
                        </h2>
                        <time
                            class="text-sm font-mono text-muted-light dark:text-muted-dark"
                            datetime="2024-07-18">July 18, 2024</time
                        >
                    </header>
                    <p
                        class="text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark/90"
                    >
                        Forget the old hacks. For most cases today, `display:
                        grid; place-items: center;` is the cleanest and most
                        reliable way to center an element both horizontally and
                        vertically within its parent. Works like a charm every
                        time.
                    </p>
                </article>
                <article
                    class="p-6 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800"
                >
                    <header class="mb-3">
                        <h2
                            class="text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark"
                        >
                            The importance of semantic HTML
                        </h2>
                        <time
                            class="text-sm font-mono text-muted-light dark:text-muted-dark"
                            datetime="2024-07-15">July 15, 2024</time
                        >
                    </header>
                    <p
                        class="text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark/90"
                    >
                        A reminder that using tags like `
                    </p><nav>
                        `, `<main>
                            `, `<article>
                                `, and `<footer>
                                    ` isn't just for organization. It's crucial
                                    for accessibility, helping screen readers
                                    understand the structure of your page. It
                                    also gives a small boost to SEO.
                                </footer>
                            </article>
                        </main>
                    </nav><p></p>
                </article>
                <article
                    class="p-6 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800"
                >
                    <header class="mb-3">
                        <h2
                            class="text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark"
                        >
                            Dark mode isn't just a trend
                        </h2>
                        <time
                            class="text-sm font-mono text-muted-light dark:text-muted-dark"
                            datetime="2024-07-12">July 12, 2024</time
                        >
                    </header>
                    <p
                        class="text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark/90"
                    >
                        Implementing a dark mode toggle has become a standard
                        user expectation. Beyond the aesthetic appeal, it
                        reduces eye strain in low-light environments and can
                        even save battery life on OLED screens. It's a
                        thoughtful feature that improves user experience.
                    </p>
                </article>
                <article
                    class="p-6 bg-surface-light dark:bg-surface-dark rounded-xl border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800"
                >
                    <header class="mb-3">
                        <h2
                            class="text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark"
                        >
                            New project launch
                        </h2>
                        <time
                            class="text-sm font-mono text-muted-light dark:text-muted-dark"
                            datetime="2024-07-10">July 10, 2024</time
                        >
                    </header>
                    <p
                        class="text-on-surface-light dark:text-on-surface-dark/90"
                    >
                        Excited to share a small side project I've been working
                        on: a minimalist pomodoro timer built with vanilla JS.
                        It's all about focus and simplicity. Check it out and
                        let me know what you think!
                    </p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>
